\par \pard\plain \s0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\kerning1\hich\af3\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs24\lang1081\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\ulnone\ulc0\b0\afs22\ab0\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang9
As mentioned above, Control Points can be upgraded by having prefabricated buildings deployed onto them once you have captured the Nav Beacon. Each Control Point can have only one upgrade, so players must choose wisely which upgrades they want. Here is a short list:}
\par \pard\plain \s0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\kerning1\hich\af3\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs24\lang1081\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 \'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls2 \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\ulnone\ulc0\b0\afs22\ab0\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang9
GARRISONS are the most basic form of upgrade, consisting of a prefabricated bunker. This upgrade doesn't unlock any new abilities or units, but simply serves as a hardened defensive point that  your enemies must destroy before they can capture it's Nav Beacon. In other words, they're best placed on Beacons you're not sure you can hold, to delay your enemy and force them to spend time (and ammo) killing it. Garrisons can be further upgraded with an assortment of heavy weapons. }
\par \pard\plain \s0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\kerning1\hich\af3\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs24\lang1081\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 \'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls2 \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\ulnone\ulc0\b0\afs22\ab0\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang9
MOBILE MECHBAYS are extremely useful structures that allow Mechs to quickly repair and rearm on the battlefield without having to wait for dropships.}
\par \pard\plain \s0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\kerning1\hich\af3\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs24\lang1081\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 \'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls2 \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\ulnone\ulc0\b0\afs22\ab0\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang9
ORBITAL UPLINKS are communications arrays that provide real-time control over assets in space. These include Orbital Strikes, which drops a barrage of artillery from space over a target area; Aerofighter Sorties, which send squadrons of Aerofighters on various missions from bombing to air superiority; and Turret Emplacements which drop small, temporary weapons platforms. We may add more functions to this in the future.}
\par \pard\plain \s0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\kerning1\hich\af3\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs24\lang1081\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 \'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls2 \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\ulnone\ulc0\b0\afs22\ab0\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang9
C3 RELAYS are a battlefield communication system that allows players to control more Mechs by increasing the bandwidth of Command & Control comms systems. Each C3 Relay placed allows you to control an additional Lance of Mechs.}
\par \pard\plain \s0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\kerning1\hich\af3\langfe1033\dbch\af3\afs24\lang1081\loch\f3\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af4\dbch\af4\loch\f4 \'95\tab}\ilvl0\ls2 \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\ulnone\ulc0\b0\afs22\ab0\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang9
VEHICLE LANDING PADS are structures that allow allied conventional ground forces to be deployed to your battlefield. Once deployed, vehicles will be steadily landed a couple of times every minute. Once landed, these allied vehicles will randomly patrol around the map.}
